why is life a daily struggle i know that many people have problmes in life but it just seems like thiers one hurdle after another in my life compared to everyone else i know so tell me other wise it's all a matter of relativity having to keep going up and down stairs may be a pain in the rear end but think just how much more of a pain if you have no legs or if the artificial ones you have make your stumps sore presently i have to type with just three finger well two finger and a thumb and you have no idea just how consuming this is of my energy my patience my time and all of the frustrations that goes with it now put that into the context of the rest of your daily activities and count the hurdles i'm not saying that 'my life is harder than yours ' i am saying that you need to view the perspectives and maybe look at just why it is that yours are such big many hurdles sash Fast bowling Equine conformation Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Professional wrestling holds Professional wrestling attacks Umpire (cricket) Archery Breastfeeding Diving Holy Spirit Hal Trosky Laws of cricket Carpal tunnel syndrome Chronic fatigue syndrome Esperanto as an international language Bob Tisdall Hurdling Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Cricket Ecology Karen Horney Bass guitar Non-standard cosmology Dairy Anal sex Nature versus nurture Aerial (dance move) Drawing Masturbation Communist Party of India (Marxist-Leninist) Janashakti Inflation Dualism (philosophy of mind) Fielding (cricket) Mattress Aikido Goodness and value theory Milton H. Erickson Animal rights Double bass Weight training Stereoscopy Meditation Stem cell Vampire Social psychology Videocon Tri-Series 2005-06 Glossary of climbing terms Spanking Massage Skateboarding trick Guinea pig Human Meaning of life Opus Dei Sinfest Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Mortification of the flesh Faster-than-light Fanny Blankers-Koen Modern geocentrism Dyson sphere Erie Canal Stress fracture Peter Singer Domestic violence Olympic med